{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"676a19b8-5684-4fea-b08a-80b4cbf83033","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n- Run `dotnet restore` to pull updated packages.\n- Update any NuGet packages that have .NET 11-specific versions (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`).\n- Run `dotnet build` and fix any breaking API changes.\n- Review the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) for breaking changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f1524465-31df-4d3d-9334-e604877739cb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward informational question - I don't need to explore any codebase since they're asking for general guidance.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the three items they mentioned.","outputTokens":337,"requestId":"F80E:392B11:6FEE7C:805404:6A0529FC"},"id":"d630783d-0d1e-4226-9f29-c5d0736ed2e5","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:48:52.074Z","parentId":"ae33f0f1-0633-439f-8e7f-36cb85f9301c"}
